To display a square with the selected color, you can create a small canvas widget in your tkinter window and update its background color with the selected color. Here's how you can modify your code to achieve that:

```python
import tkinter as tk
from tkinter import colorchooser, filedialog
import analiz

color = ""  # Variable to store the selected color
file_path = ""  # Variable to store the selected file path

def show_color_picker():
    global color
    color = colorchooser.askcolor(title="Выберите цвет")
    if color[1]:
        print("Выбранный цвет:", color[1])
        update_color_square()  # Call function to update color square

def update_color_square():
    canvas.config(bg=color[1])  # Update the background color of the canvas

# ... (rest of your code) ...

# Create a canvas for the color square
canvas = tk.Canvas(window, width=50, height=50, bg=color[1])
canvas.pack(anchor="nw", padx=6, pady=6)

# ... (rest of your code) ...
```

This code adds a canvas widget to your tkinter window, and when the user selects a color, it updates the background color of the canvas to the selected color. Make sure to create the canvas before using the `update_color_square` function.
